description: {"blocks":[{"key":"3f55b","text":"Plasmid extraction and purification, based on Vazyme Mini-prep Kit manual.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"831ci","text":"Pellet bacteria culture in a 1.6mL centrifugation tube at 13,000rpm for 1 minute. Decant supernatant. The pellet in the tube can be stored in -20 freezer if time not enough for the following steps.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a1unm","text":"Add 250uL of resuspension solution (P1 with RNase) and vortex. After adding RNase into the P1, P1 is stored in 4 degree refrigerator.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f4jsf","text":"Add 250uL of lysis solution (P2) and invert gently 4-6 times. P2 contains NaOH, and must keep tightly closed.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6fm97","text":"Add 350uL of neutralization solution (P3) and invert gently 4-6 times. Do not vortex, which will break bacteria genomic DNA and genomic DNA fragments will contaminate purified plasmids.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dugaq","text":"Take the clear supernatant, without any white protein cloud. Bind the DNA to the column by decanting.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3l1sh","text":"Wash the column with 600uL of wash solution (PW2) and centrifuge for 1 minute. Remind adding pure ethanol into PW2 as indicated on the bottle.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5essi","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":"60","guid":"084163F0E6924B10BE0409D9A4FA1347","id":"1843","label":"","preset":[]}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4tesq","text":"Discard the flow-through, wash again with 600uL of PW2, and centrifuge for 1 minute. Discard the flow-through and centrifuge the column again for 2 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9ein5","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":180,"guid":"D9BA7E4B230F4D7CA58E095EFF3EE93D","id":"1844","label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"20far","text":"Keep the cap open and wait until no ethanol smell. Move the column into a new centrifugation tube. Elute the purified DNA with 50uL of elution buffer (TE; 10 mM Tris-Cl, 1 mM EDTA). Then, centrifuge for 1 minutes. Collect the flow-through, which is the plasmid DNA. Because pET28 based is low-copy plasmid, pre-warm TE to 50 degree helps the elution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2j7e6","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":"60","guid":"4016219F702040D78A6C11D1135AA8CE","id":"1845","label":"","preset":[]}}}}
